text: Week-End in Havana (also known as A Week-End in Havana and That Week-End in Havana) is a 1941 American romantic musical comedy movie directed by Walter Lang. It stars Alice Faye, Carmen Miranda, John Payne, Cesar Romero. It was distributed by 20th Century Fox and is the follow up to the 1940 movie Down Argentine Way and That Night in Rio. ==Other websites== * * Category:1941 movies Category:1940s romance movies Category:American musical movies Category:American romantic comedy movies Category:Movies set in Cuba Category:Movies directed by Walter Lang
